  "subject": "Fix: use conditional checkout for push events",
  "commit_message": "Fix: use conditional checkout for push events\n\nOn push events, checkout-gerrit-change-action ran with an\nempty GERRIT_REFSPEC causing git fetch origin to check out\nan unpredictable FETCH_HEAD commit. This resulted in a\nmissing .gitreview file and workflow failure.\n\nAdd conditional checkout logic for three scenarios:\n- push: 10s replication delay then actions/checkout\n- workflow_dispatch with Gerrit: checkout-gerrit-change\n- workflow_dispatch with GERRIT_DISABLED: actions/checkout\n\nAlso upgrade checkout-gerrit-change-action v0.9 to v1.0.1\nand add the missing gerrit-project input.\n\nIssue-ID: CIMAN-33\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>\nChange-Id: I59f52b64d8224f6ca9edc4deb481169c661f2675\nSigned-off-by: Matthew Watkins <mwatkins@linuxfoundation.org>\n",
